{"TopicId":209944,"ForumId":112,"TopicTitle":"Will we need Bulldozers for KSP2 to get rid of rocks etc?","CreatedByName":"Anth","CreatedById":161238,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-09-30T00:38:08Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Anth","CreatedById":161238,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-09-30T00:38:08Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI was watching youtube videos with people using rovers and trying to navigate terrain with Parallax 2.0 with colliders on. That was problematic \u003Cimg alt=\u0022;)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022;)\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWill we need Bulldozers or/and Engineers to be able to clear areas?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"shdwlrd","CreatedById":113880,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-09-30T01:07:36Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSince the colony parts will be on stilts, it shouldn\u0027t be necessary. But it\u2019s KSP, so there\u0027s nothing to stop you trying.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Anth","CreatedById":161238,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-09-30T01:16:32Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224180493\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022209944\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221664500056\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022113880\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022shdwlrd\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n7 minutes ago, shdwlrd said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSince the colony parts will be on stilts, it shouldn\u0027t be necessary. But it\u2019s KSP, so there\u0027s nothing to stop you trying.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYeah, but its not like a player is going to be limited to the colony bases, they will still use rovers on the normal terrain.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"shdwlrd","CreatedById":113880,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-09-30T01:38:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224180496\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022209944\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221664500592\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022161238\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Anth12\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 minutes ago, Anth12 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYeah, but its not like a player is going to be limited to the colony bases, they will still use rovers on the normal terrain.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAre you expecting rovers to behave like the Snowrunner vehicles? The smallest rock send the rover flying? No, I don\u0027t see that happening.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s been confirmed that only the larger scatter will have colliders.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Anth","CreatedById":161238,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-09-30T02:05:49Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224180500\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022209944\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221664501891\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022113880\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022shdwlrd\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n27 minutes ago, shdwlrd said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s been confirmed that only the larger scatter will have colliders.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOh. That\u0027s good to know thanks\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"mcwaffles2003","CreatedById":180102,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-09-30T15:32:33Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224180500\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022209944\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221664501891\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022113880\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022shdwlrd\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n13 hours ago, shdwlrd said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s been confirmed that only the larger scatter will have colliders.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt was?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"The Aziz","CreatedById":150811,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-09-30T17:16:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedauthorid=\u0022205123\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed4343192264\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/204240-show-and-tell-terrain-progress/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0026amp;comment=4015553\u0026amp;embedComment=4015553\u0026amp;embedDo=findComment\u0022 style=\u0022height:320px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nyes.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"shdwlrd","CreatedById":113880,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-09-30T17:21:58Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224180651\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022209944\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221664551953\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022180102\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022mcwaffles2003\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, mcwaffles2003 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt was?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes, well more phrased; we\u0027re trying to find the best size cut off for rock colliders. I don\u0027t have the patience find the thread. It\u0027s in the one of the S\u0026amp;T or dev diary where they are showing a rocket on the Mun with scatter everywhere. Nate mentioned that not all the scatter shown will have colliders. Someone pointed out that not all the rocks are causing shadows. So speculation at the time was anything that didn\u0027t cause a shadow doesn\u0027t have colliders.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNinja\u0027d by \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/150811-the-aziz/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022150811\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/150811-the-aziz/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@The Aziz\u003C/a\u003E; and thanks for posting the thread.\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222022-09-30T17:24:10Z\u0022 title=\u002209/30/2022 05:24  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00221 yr\u0022\u003ESeptember 30, 2022\u003C/time\u003E by shdwlrd\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Anth","CreatedById":161238,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-09-30T19:39:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224180686\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022209944\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221664558214\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022150811\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022The Aziz\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, The Aziz said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nyes.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks. I made a comment over on that post. Parallax 2.0 definitely worried me for a fun experience in KSP2\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}